br.usp.poli.takiyama.prv
Class Binding

java.lang.Object
  br.usp.poli.takiyama.prv.Binding

public class Binding
extends java.lang.Object

A binding is an ordered pair of terms (t1, t2). The first term (t1) must be a LogicalVariable and the second term (t2) may be a Constant or another LogicalVariable. We say that t2 replaces t1.

Author:
Felipe Takiyama

isValid

public boolean isValid()
Returns true if:
  • The second term is a Constant and it belongs to first term's population or
  • The second term is a LogicalVariable and both terms have the same population

    Returns:
    true if second term is in first term's population or if second term and first term have the same population, false otherwise.
